The paper proposes a pipeline for multi-parametric quantitative MRI image computing that involves compressed sensing reconstruction and deep learned quantitative inference. The use of compressed sensing and deep learning techniques suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also incorporates spatiotemporal regularizations, which could place it in the information theory (cs.IT) or numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
